# SentinelMem — frontend (Vite) environment.
#
# All variables here are OPTIONAL and PUBLIC: anything prefixed VITE_ is embedded
# into the client bundle at build time. NEVER put secrets here.
#   ❌ do NOT add: OLLAMA_KEY, SUI_SECRET_KEY, MEMWAL_PRIVATE_KEY, anything in .sentinel/
# Those belong only to the local agent server (pnpm sentinel:serve), never the UI.

# URL of a hosted agent server (the `pnpm sentinel:serve` backend) that powers the
# in-app "Investigate" button. Must be HTTPS when the site is served over HTTPS
# (browsers block https→http "mixed content"). Leave unset on a static deploy:
# the inspector stays read-only and Investigate is disabled.
# VITE_AGENT_URL=https://your-agent-server.example

# Pin a trusted signer public key (base64 Ed25519 SPKI) for the in-browser
# "memory verified" check. If unset, the UI trusts the signerPublicKey published
# in the memory index (public/sentinel-memory.json).
# VITE_SENTINEL_SIGNER=
